oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Nashville Cats program - Reggie Young - 2008-05-03 - Part 2 only
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Program on the life and career of guitarist Reggie Young. Recorded from the Ford Theater at the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum on May 3, 2008. Part 2 only. Part 1 is apparently missing.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Reggie Young
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Interview program hosted by Bill Lloyd. Includes selected excerpts from recordings, audio from video. Performances of selected songs, solos and guitar introductions from "Cry Like A Baby" -- "Hooked On A Feeling" -- "I Can Help" -- "Son Of A Preacher Man" -- "Drift Away" -- "In The Ghetto" -- "Natchez Trace" with Jennifer Young
